bug.short_desc: 412 Precondition Failed - during PUT when modifying a contact

long_desc.thetext:
Created an attachment (id=1562) syslog create/modify contacts
Hello,
playing with cyrus's beta of the cal/carddav extension, I came accross the following issue: Creating new contacts seems to work, but modifying fails. I used two different clients to test, a roundcube webmail on the same host with the rcmcarddav plugin and thunderbird with inverse sogo connector. If you tell me how to increase/decrease cyrus's syslog output, I may can provide more information about this.
I attached some syslog of both attempts.
Due to the time consuming process of building from source I first tested the version, packaged with debian jessie. I don't know how much the the caldav code differs from the current 2.5.x stable version.
Best regards, Christian

This was resolved with commit https://git.cyrus.foundation/rIb891191c093aed2e9baf34d03d082ae23d6acb4d
If you want to continue with the 2.4.17 code you will have to pull the latest code in the caldav-2.4 branch from git.
All new development on CalDAV/CardDAV is being done on the master branch (3.x)
